data.enText: being the only one of its kind

data.chText: 每个人的指纹都是独一无二的。

data.text: You can use absolutely , totally or almost with unique in this meaning.
作此义时可用absolutely、totally或almost 修饰unique。

data.chText: 预展提供了看展览但不挨挤的难得机会。
data.enText: The preview offers a unique opportunity to see the show without the crowds.

data.chText: 这项协议给予这家公司向东欧输出商品的特殊地位。
data.enText: The deal will put the company in a unique position to export goods to Eastern Europe.

data.text: You can use more , very , etc. with unique in this meaning.

data.chText: （某人、地或事物）独具的，特有的
data.enText: belonging to or connected with one particular person, place or thing
an atmosphere that is unique to New York

data.chText: 树袋熊是澳大利亚独有的。
data.enText: The koala is unique to Australia.

data.chText: 她以往的经历使她格外适合领导这场运动。
data.enText: Her past experience made her uniquely suited to lead the campaign.

data.chText: 唯有英国无须面对大量失业的问题。
data.enText: The UK, uniquely, has not had to face the problem of mass unemployment.

data.chText: 他是个天赋异禀的天才教师。
data.enText: He was a uniquely gifted teacher.

data.chText: 这位作者强调个人的独特性。
data.enText: The author stresses the uniqueness of the individual.

means: (某人、地或事物)独具的，特有的

tr: highly unusual or rare but not the single instance
example: had unique ability in raising funds
he is alone in the field of microbiology
this theory is altogether alone in its penetration of the problem
Bach was unique in his handling of counterpoint
a breakdown of law unparalleled in our history

tr: the single one of its kind
example: the unique existing example of Donne's handwriting
a unique copy of an ancient manuscript
certain types of problems have unique solutions

value.def: Something that is unique is the only one of its kind.

example.tran: 每个人的签名都是独一无二的。

example.ex: The area has its own unique language, Catalan.
example.tran: 这个地区有自己单独的语言，加泰罗尼亚语。

example.ex: Because of the extreme cold, the Antarctic is a uniquely fragile environment...
example.tran: 极度严寒造成了南极地区绝无仅有的脆弱环境。

example.ex: Uniquely among the great world religions, Buddhism is rooted only in the universal experience of suffering known to all human beings.
example.tran: 与世界其他主要宗教不同的是，佛教是唯一基于全人类所共知的苦难而产生发展起来的。

example.ex: Each time I returned I was struck by the uniqueness of Australia and its people.
example.tran: 每次返回，我都会惊讶于澳大利亚及其国民的与众不同。

value.def: You can use unique to describe things that you admire because they are very unusual and special.

example.tran: 布雷特的歌声无与伦比。

example.ex: Kauffman was a woman of unique talent and determination.
example.tran: 考夫曼是一个有着超群才智和决断力的女子。

example.ex: ...people who consider themselves uniquely qualified to be president of the United States.
example.tran: 认为自己最能胜任美国总统一职的人

example.ex: ...a festival ambience that is uniquely conducive to the absorption of serious music.
example.tran: 特别适合欣赏严肃音乐的节日氛围

value.def: If something is unique to one thing, person, group, or place, it concerns or belongs only to that thing, person, group, or place.

example.ex: No one knows for sure why adolescence is unique to humans...
example.tran: 没有人确切地知道为什么只有人类才会经历青春期。

example.ex: This interesting and charming creature is unique to Borneo.
example.tran: 这种有趣迷人的动物是婆罗洲独有的。
这个问题不是美国所独有的。
